In  [[Medicine]] and allied fields, '''diathesis''' (from Greek διάθεσις) is a hereditary or constitutional predisposition to a disease or other disorder.<ref>{{cite book |title=Empirical studies in diathesis |last=Andersen |first=Paul Kent |year=1994 |publisher=Nodus Publikationen |isbn=9783893232574 }}</ref>

''Atopic diathesis'' is a predisposition to develop one or more of [[hay fever]], [[allergic rhinitis]], [[bronchial asthma]], or [[atopic dermatitis]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Textbook of Clinical Dermatology|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sMopbRcIrZMC|page=26|last=Sehgal|first=Virendra N.|publisher=[[Jaypee Brothers]]|location=[[New Delhi]]|year=2004|accessdate=15 April 2013}}</ref>

