{{BLP sources|date=April 2017}}{{other people||Richard Clark (disambiguation)}}'''Richard A.F. Clark''' is a dermatologist and biomedical engineer{{Citation needed|date=September 2011}} currently at the [[State University of New York at Stony Brook]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bme.stonybrook.edu/people/faculty/r_clark.html|title=Richard A. F. Clark, M.D.|website=www.bme.stonybrook.edu|access-date=2017-04-12}}</ref> in [[Stony Brook, New York|Stony Brook]], [[New York (state)|New York]]. Clark co-edited, with Peter M. Henson, of ''The Molecular and Cellular Biology of Wound Repair'' (Plenum Press, 1988) and is a contributor to [[wound repair]], [[dermatology]], and [[angiogenesis]] research. In addition, he is also a member of the board of directors of the [[Society for Investigative Dermatology]].
Clark graduated from the [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] and has worked at the [[Massachusetts General Hospital]]. He was previously professor at [[Harvard University]]. He is now a professor at [[State University of New York at Stony Brook]].
