[[Image:Saavi logo.jpg|thumb|right]] The '''South African AIDS Vaccine Initiative''' or '''SAAVI''' is a [[South Africa]]n organisation with the mission of coordinating the [[research and development]] of [[HIV vaccines]] in and for South Africa.
==History== SAAVI was established in 1999 by the South African government as a project of the [[South African Medical Research Council]].
==Partners== SAAVI frequently partners with the [[HIV Vaccine Trials Network]].{{Citation needed|date=June 2011}}
==Funding problems== In June 2009, SAAVI announced that it was testing a new HIV vaccine candidate but suspended all further vaccine development indefinitely due to lack of funds.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://washingtonexaminer.com/world/2009/07/south-africa-launches-aids-vaccine-trial-slashes-research-funding |title=South Africa launches AIDS vaccine trial but slashes research funding |first=Michelle |last=Faul |publisher=[[Washington Examiner]] |work=washingtonexaminer.com |date=20 June 2009 |accessdate=24 June 2011}}</ref>
