{{Suicide sidebar}}
'''Suicide in Mozambique''' is a significant national social issue due to its high rate. [[Mozambique]] is also [[Africa]]'s most suicide-prone area.<ref name="eNCa">{{cite web|title=Mozambique 'No 1 suicide nation in Africa'|url=https://www.enca.com/mozambique-no-1-suicide-nation-africa|publisher=eNCa|accessdate=31 January 2016}}</ref> According to a report published by [[World Health Organization]] published in 2012, 1.52% of all deaths in the country are caused by [[suicide]].<ref name="World Life Expectancy">{{cite web|title=Suicide in Mozambique|url=http://www.worldlifeexpectancy.com/mozambique-suicide|accessdate=31 January 2016}}</ref><ref name="BMJ">{{cite web|title=Suicide in Mozambique: evidence from 10 years mortuary data from forensic services at Maputo Central Hospital, Maputo city|url=http://injuryprevention.bmj.com/content/18/Suppl_1/A166.1.full.pdf+html|publisher=Injury prevention|accessdate=31 January 2016}}</ref>

